---
import Interior from "../layouts/Interior.astro";
import { values, vision } from "../data/site";
---

<Interior
	title="New Life | What We Believe"
	description="It starts and ends with a Person: Jesus Christ — crucified, risen, and Lord. What we believe at New Life Grand Rapids."
	kicker="About New Life"
	heading="What We Believe"
>
	<!-- Section 2 — The floor (the Person) -->
	<section class="section creed">
		<div class="creed__glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
		<div class="container creed__inner">
			<p class="eyebrow reveal">It starts and ends with a Person.</p>
			<p class="creed__sub reveal">Not a doctrine about him. Him.</p>
			<p class="creed__name reveal">
				Jesus Christ<span>— crucified, risen, and Lord.</span>
			</p>
			<div class="creed__body reveal">
				<p>
					Before the church had a single page of the New Testament to argue over, it had a
					confession: <strong>Jesus is Lord.</strong>
				</p>
				<p>
					Rome demanded its people declare <em>Caesar is Lord</em> — and Christians went to their
					deaths rather than say it of anyone but Jesus. That's the ground we stand on. That's the
					line.
				</p>
				<p>
					A person who confesses Christ crucified and risen is our family, even where we see things
					differently. A teaching that denies him isn't a disagreement — it's a different faith.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 3 — What he asks -->
	<section class="section prose-block prose-block--tinted">
		<div class="container">
			<p class="eyebrow reveal">What he asks</p>
			<h2 class="prose-block__title reveal">Three commands.</h2>
			<div class="commands__pair">
				<div class="command-card reveal">
					<span class="command-card__n">01</span>
					<h3>Love God</h3>
					<p>with everything you are.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="command-card reveal" style="--delay:90ms">
					<span class="command-card__n">02</span>
					<h3>Love people</h3>
					<p>as yourself.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="command-card command-card--derived reveal">
				<span class="command-card__n">03</span>
				<h3>Be one</h3>
				<p>with the rest of Christ's church.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="prose-block__body">
				<p class="reveal">That's our whole position.</p>
			</div>
			<p class="commands__line reveal">Love God, love people, be one.</p>
			<div class="prose-block__body">
				<p class="reveal">
					The rest is just working out what these three mean. And the third grows right out of the
					first two: when you love the people God loves, you find yourself loving his whole family —
					the ones who read a verse differently standing right alongside you. It's what Jesus prayed
					for the night before he died — that his people would be one, <strong>so the world would
					know</strong> he was sent. Not the reward for finally agreeing. The witness itself.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 4 — Tribalism, the counterfeit -->
	<section class="section prose-block prose-block--tinted">
		<div class="container">
			<p class="eyebrow reveal">The counterfeit</p>
			<h2 class="prose-block__title reveal">Tribalism is the oldest religious instinct there is.</h2>
			<div class="prose-block__body">
				<p class="reveal">
					It drew the line between Jew and Samaritan, between Pharisee and Sadducee, between the
					clean and the unclean — and every time, the people drawing it were certain they were
					defending righteousness.
				</p>
				<p class="reveal">
					Jesus walked straight through those lines. He talked with the woman at the well, made a
					Samaritan the hero of his story, and saved his sharpest words not for sinners but for the
					religious insiders who had mistaken their fences for faithfulness.
				</p>
			</div>
			<p class="rest-pull reveal">
				Holiness is to be set apart for God. Tribalism is the inversion — setting people apart from
				one another.
			</p>
			<div class="prose-block__body">
				<p class="reveal">
					A counterfeit holiness — one that denies the cross the very thing it accomplished:
					making us one.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 5 — What this means (and what it doesn't) -->
	<section class="section prose-block">
		<div class="container">
			<p class="eyebrow reveal">What this means</p>
			<h2 class="prose-block__title reveal">Let's be clear.</h2>
			<div class="clarify">
				<ul class="clarify__col clarify__col--not">
					<li class="reveal">This does <strong>not</strong> mean doctrine doesn't matter. It does.</li>
					<li class="reveal">This does <strong>not</strong> mean we're soft on our convictions. We're not.</li>
					<li class="reveal">This does <strong>not</strong> mean visiting or praying for another church endorses everything they believe.</li>
					<li class="reveal">This does <strong>not</strong> mean working alongside unbelievers or other organizations endorses everything they stand for.</li>
				</ul>
				<ul class="clarify__col clarify__col--does">
					<li class="reveal">We hold our convictions firmly <em>and</em> refuse to break fellowship with believers who land somewhere different on secondary things.</li>
					<li class="reveal">We think using theology as a cover for tribalism is a real and present danger — maybe the more common one.</li>
					<li class="reveal">The honest test isn't whether you can tolerate people outside the faith. It's whether you can pray with a brother or sister <em>inside</em> it who disagrees with you.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 6 — Fellowship and partnership -->
	<section class="section prose-block">
		<div class="container">
			<p class="eyebrow reveal">One more distinction</p>
			<h2 class="prose-block__title reveal">Fellowship and partnership aren't the same thing.</h2>
			<div class="prose-block__body">
				<p class="reveal">
					Fellowship is what we owe every believer: if you confess Christ crucified and risen,
					you're family — we pray with you, honor you, and refuse to treat you as an enemy, no
					matter where you land on the rest.
				</p>
				<p class="reveal">
					Partnership is narrower. The question is practical: can we do this particular work well
					together, or would our differences keep getting in the way? Often they don't, and we
					build. Sometimes they'd put our people in the middle of conflict the work doesn't need —
					and holding back there isn't a verdict on anyone's faithfulness, just honesty that it's
					better done apart.
				</p>
			</div>
			<p class="rest-pull reveal">
				Fellowship is never the price of agreement; partnership is simply matched to the task.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 7 — Where the rest lives + CTA -->
	<section class="section prose-block prose-block--tinted">
		<div class="container">
			<p class="eyebrow reveal">Where the rest lives</p>
			<h2 class="prose-block__title reveal">So where's everything else?</h2>
			<div class="prose-block__body">
				<p class="reveal">
					The authority of Scripture. The nature of Christ. Baptism. Sexuality and gender. The end
					times. Church government. Our people hold real, considered convictions about all of it —
					and they don't all land in the same place. We don't hand you the church's official
					position on these, because the church doesn't have one. We have the one foundation — the
					Person himself — and then people who love Jesus, read carefully, and dialogue with each
					other in the open.
				</p>
			</div>
			<p class="rest-pull reveal">
				That's not a gap we're apologizing for. It is the truth about who we are and what we hold
				dear. The moment we mandate answers to these, we're back to dividing over them.
			</p>
			<div class="prose-block__body">
				<p class="reveal">
					So these aren't things we settle on a webpage, where there's no relationship to hold them
					and no room for you to push back. They belong in person. Over a table. In the life of a
					community you can actually walk into.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="rest-cta reveal">
				<p>So come ask. That's where we do our best thinking anyway.</p>
				<a class="button button--primary" href="/visit">Plan a Visit</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 8 — The honest challenge -->
	<section class="section challenge">
		<div class="container">
			<p class="eyebrow reveal">One honest question</p>
			<blockquote class="challenge__quote reveal">
				It shouldn't be harder to fellowship with a believer who disagrees with you in part than
				with someone who doesn't share your faith at all.
			</blockquote>
			<p class="challenge__body reveal">
				Worth asking why. Usually it's not that truth matters more to us — it's that the insider
				threatens our certainty and the outsider doesn't. Unity doesn't ask you to relinquish your
				convictions, only that we become more aware of the lure of tribalism and of the presence of
				Christ in the person across the table.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 9 — Values + vision strip -->
	<section class="section section--final identity-strip">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="section-heading reveal">
				<p class="eyebrow">The identity underneath it</p>
				<h2>The values and vision we carry.</h2>
			</div>

			<div class="value-grid">
				{values.map((v, i) => (
					<article class="value-card reveal" style={`--delay:${i * 60}ms`}>
						<h3>{v.title}</h3>
						<p>{v.body}</p>
					</article>
				))}
			</div>

			<div class="identity-strip__vision">
				<p class="eyebrow reveal">Our Vision</p>
				<ul class="vision-line">
					{vision.map((v, i) => (
						<li class="reveal" style={`--delay:${i * 90}ms`}>{v.title}</li>
					))}
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Interior>

<style>
	/* --- Section 2: the Person --- */
	.creed {
		padding-top: 4rem;
		padding-bottom: 6rem;
		overflow: hidden;
		text-align: center;
	}
	.creed__inner {
		max-width: 72ch;
	}
	.creed__glow {
		position: absolute;
		top: 40%;
		left: 50%;
		width: min(44rem, 92vw);
		height: min(44rem, 92vw);
		transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
		background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(242, 210, 162, 0.18), transparent 62%);
		filter: blur(24px);
		pointer-events: none;
		z-index: 0;
		animation: creedBreathe 9s ease-in-out infinite;
	}
	.creed__inner > * {
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
	}
	.creed__sub {
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		margin: 0.4rem 0 1.6rem;
	}
	.creed__name {
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", "Book Antiqua", Georgia, serif;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.04em;
		line-height: 0.98;
		font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 7.5vw, 5.6rem);
		max-width: 22ch;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}
	.creed__name span {
		display: block;
		font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.4vw, 1.7rem);
		letter-spacing: 0;
		color: var(--gold);
		margin-top: 0.8rem;
	}
	.creed__body {
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.22rem);
		line-height: 1.65;
		max-width: 54ch;
		margin: 2.6rem auto 0;
		text-align: left;
	}
	.creed__body p {
		margin: 0;
	}
	.creed__body p + p {
		margin-top: 1.15rem;
	}
	.creed__body strong {
		color: var(--text);
	}
	.creed__body em {
		color: var(--text);
		font-style: italic;
	}

	/* --- Prose sections (3, 4, 5, 7) --- */
	.prose-block {
		padding: 4rem 0;
	}
	.prose-block--tinted {
		background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.015), transparent);
		border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
	}
	.prose-block__title {
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", Georgia, serif;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
		line-height: 1.05;
		font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4.4vw, 3rem);
		max-width: 20ch;
		margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
	}
	.prose-block__body {
		max-width: 62ch;
		margin-top: 1.6rem;
		display: grid;
		gap: 1.2rem;
	}
	.prose-block__body p {
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 1.8vw, 1.18rem);
		line-height: 1.68;
	}
	.prose-block__body em {
		color: var(--text);
		font-style: italic;
	}
	.prose-block__body strong {
		color: var(--text);
	}

	/* --- Section 4: command cards --- */
	.commands__pair {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.1rem;
		margin-top: 1.8rem;
	}
	.command-card {
		position: relative;
		padding: 1.6rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--line);
		border-radius: 18px;
		background: var(--panel);
	}
	.command-card__n {
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", Georgia, serif;
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.2em;
		color: var(--gold);
	}
	.command-card h3 {
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", Georgia, serif;
		font-size: 1.6rem;
		margin: 0.4rem 0 0.2rem;
	}
	.command-card p {
		color: var(--muted);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.command-card--derived {
		margin-top: 1.4rem;
		max-width: 62ch;
		border-color: var(--gold-soft);
		background: linear-gradient(120deg, rgba(242, 210, 162, 0.1), var(--panel));
	}
	.command-card--derived h3 {
		color: var(--gold-strong);
	}
	.commands__line {
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", Georgia, serif;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.4vw, 2.3rem);
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--text);
		margin: 1.8rem 0 0;
	}

	/* --- Section 5: clarify columns --- */
	.clarify {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.6rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}
	.clarify__col {
		list-style: none;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0;
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.9rem;
		align-content: start;
	}
	.clarify__col li {
		position: relative;
		padding: 1rem 1.1rem 1rem 2.4rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--line);
		border-radius: 14px;
		background: var(--panel);
		color: var(--muted);
		line-height: 1.5;
	}
	.clarify__col li strong {
		color: var(--text);
	}
	.clarify__col li em {
		color: var(--text);
		font-style: italic;
	}
	.clarify__col li::before {
		position: absolute;
		left: 0.95rem;
		top: 1rem;
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", Georgia, serif;
	}
	.clarify__col--not li::before {
		content: "×";
		color: var(--rose);
	}
	.clarify__col--does li {
		border-color: var(--gold-soft);
	}
	.clarify__col--does li::before {
		content: "✓";
		color: var(--gold);
	}

	/* --- Section 6: challenge --- */
	.challenge__quote {
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", Georgia, serif;
		font-weight: 500;
		font-style: italic;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		line-height: 1.32;
		font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.6vw, 2.5rem);
		color: var(--text);
		max-width: 24ch;
		margin: 0.8rem 0 0;
		padding-left: 1.4rem;
		border-left: 2px solid var(--gold-soft);
	}
	.challenge__body {
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 1.8vw, 1.18rem);
		line-height: 1.68;
		max-width: 58ch;
		margin-top: 1.6rem;
	}

	/* --- Section 6: pull line + CTA --- */
	.rest-pull {
		max-width: 40ch;
		margin: 1.6rem 0 0;
		padding-left: 1.4rem;
		border-left: 2px solid var(--gold-soft);
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", Georgia, serif;
		font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.8vw, 1.9rem);
		line-height: 1.35;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		color: var(--text);
	}
	.rest-cta {
		margin-top: 2.2rem;
		padding: 1.8rem;
		border: 1px solid var(--gold-soft);
		border-radius: 1.4rem;
		background: linear-gradient(120deg, rgba(242, 210, 162, 0.08), var(--panel));
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 1.2rem;
	}
	.rest-cta p {
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", Georgia, serif;
		font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.6vw, 1.7rem);
		color: var(--text);
		margin: 0;
		max-width: 24ch;
	}

	/* --- Section 8: identity strip --- */
	.identity-strip__vision {
		margin-top: 2.6rem;
		padding-top: 1.8rem;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
	}
	.vision-line {
		list-style: none;
		margin: 0.8rem 0 0;
		padding: 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
	}
	.vision-line li {
		font-family: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", Georgia, serif;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
		color: var(--text);
		position: relative;
	}
	.vision-line li:not(:last-child)::after {
		content: "·";
		color: var(--gold);
		margin-left: 1.4rem;
	}

	/* --- Scoped motion: rise-in on scroll --- */
	.reveal {
		opacity: 0;
		transform: translateY(28px);
		filter: blur(10px);
		will-change: transform, opacity, filter;
	}
	.reveal.is-visible {
		animation: riseIn 0.9s ease both;
		animation-delay: var(--delay, 0ms);
	}

	@keyframes creedBreathe {
		0%, 100% {
			opacity: 0.7;
			transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(0.97);
		}
		50% {
			opacity: 1;
			transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1.05);
		}
	}

	@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
		.reveal {
			opacity: 1 !important;
			transform: none !important;
			filter: none !important;
			animation: none !important;
		}
		.creed__glow {
			animation: none !important;
		}
	}
</style>

<noscript>
	<style>
		.reveal { opacity: 1 !important; transform: none !important; filter: none !important; }
	</style>
</noscript>

<script>
	const els = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>(".reveal");
	const io = new IntersectionObserver(
		(entries) => {
			for (const entry of entries) {
				if (entry.isIntersecting) {
					entry.target.classList.add("is-visible");
					io.unobserve(entry.target);
				}
			}
		},
		{ rootMargin: "0px 0px -12% 0px", threshold: 0.12 },
	);
	els.forEach((el) => io.observe(el));
</script>
